FBIS4-3864 "drchi080_a_94028" FBIS-CHI-94-080 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General UN Chief Expresses Regret Over Nixon's Death UN Chief Expresses Regret Over Nixon's Death OW2304223094 Beijing XINHUA in English 2056 GMT 23 Apr 94 OW2304223094 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] United Nations, April 23 (XINHUA) -- U.N. Secretary- General Butrus Butrus-Ghali today expressed his regret of the death of former U.S. President Richard Nixon, according to a U.N. spokesman. Nixon, the 37th president of the United States, died of stroke on Friday [22 April], at the age of 81. The spokesman said "the secretary-general had known Mr. Nixon for many years. The former President's impact in the field of international relations was especially significant." The secretary-general has extended his condolences to the Nixon family, as well as to the government and the people of the United States, he said.
